{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778557438,"nonce":"Qyq5mWMVNiEavjZSacW54U1TwbU=","message":"**MVP discriminator outcome — did NOT split (2026-05-11)** — `410d7ac` ran the corrected 4-model MVP. Result:\n\n```\nΔv_regulator = +0.775 ± 0.034 (SEM, n=5)\nΔv_tracker   = +0.776 ± 0.034 (SEM, n=5)\n```\n\nStatistically identical. Both architectures show ~78% velocity inflation under `LinearDynamicsAdversary` (ΔA·x at eta_max=0.1, 5 PGD inner steps, 500 adversarial batches on top of 1000 warmup, n_replicates=5, seed=42).\n\nThe Gemini decoupling-via-parameterisation prediction (regulator → +Δv, tracker → ≈0) is **not supported** by this MVP. The regulator-inflation claim itself IS supported (linear controllers inflate velocity strongly under adversarial training).\n\nTracker `u_ff` utilization: baseline `|u_ff|_max = 0.021`, adversarial `|u_ff|_max = 0.052` — adversarial training did engage the feedforward channel 4× more than baseline, but still vastly smaller than the K-driven feedback. The optimizer prefers a K-heavy solution.\n\n## Implications for full-scope d448c9d\n\nThe MVP rules out the most optimistic version of the decoupling hypothesis (\"adding u_ff to a linear controller is sufficient to prevent velocity inflation\"). It does NOT rule out:\n\n1. A longer-training version (500 adversarial batches may be insufficient for the optimizer to find the decoupled solution)\n2. A structurally different tracker design (free `u_ff(t)` parameter without input-dependence may be too inexpressive)\n3. The non-linear architectures from variants 3 (affine recurrent) and 4 (GRU)\n\nRecommended next steps before committing to the full d448c9d sweep:\n- Extend the MVP with longer adversarial training (e.g. 2000-5000 batches) using the `--resume` mechanism — cheap, since the warmup-phase model is already on disk\n- If the longer-training version still doesn't split, the parameterisation-alone hypothesis is dead and the d448c9d sweep should pivot toward affine recurrent + GRU directly\n\nSee `410d7ac` for the full corrected MVP report (commits `45cc2db` + `dfac0d0`, auth `4696b654`).","files":null}]}